.TH "acpi_create_platform_device" 9 "acpi_create_platform_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_create_platform_device \- Create platform device for ACPI device node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct platform_device *" acpi_create_platform_device
.BI "(struct acpi_device *adev "  ","
.BI "struct property_entry *properties "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
ACPI device node to create a platform device for.
.IP "properties" 12
Optional collection of build-in properties.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check if the given \fIadev\fP can be represented as a platform device and, if
that's the case, create and register a platform device, populate its common
resources and returns a pointer to it.  Otherwise, return NULL.

Name of the platform device will be the same as \fIadev\fP's.
